cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DB

This paper discusses the use of hypothesis generation systems in the biomedical field, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques (cs.CL and cs.IR). The paper also introduces new metrics for evaluating the performance of these systems (cs.LG) and discusses the potential for these systems to become the basis of intelligent automated discovery systems (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of data and validation methods (cs.DB).
